# Agent Context (CLAUDE.md) - TypeScript / Node stack

> This repo applies the [Excellence Standards - Engineering (ESE)](.standards/STANDARDS.md). These instructions apply to any AI coding agent working in this repository.

## Bootstrap

Run the bootstrap script before any other work if this project has unfilled ESE placeholders. See the canonical AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md for the full bootstrap check and procedure.

## Stack-specific commands

**Package manager.** This project uses `npm` (replace with `pnpm` / `yarn` / `bun` if different). Replace `npm run` with your chosen manager's equivalent.

**Test runner.** Before declaring a feature complete, run:

```
npm test
```

For a tighter loop during development (replace `jest` with `vitest` / `mocha` if different):

```
npx jest <specific-test-file> --watch
```

**Type check.** Always run the compiler:

```
npx tsc --noEmit
```

This catches type errors without emitting build output; cheaper than a full build.

**Lint.** This project uses `eslint` (plus `prettier` for formatting):

```
npx eslint .
npx prettier --check .
```

**Build.** For a library or application build:

```
npm run build
```

**Pre-commit.** Install the hook once per clone:

```
ln -sf ../../scripts/pre-commit .git/hooks/pre-commit
```

## TypeScript / Node-specific ESE notes

- Use strict TypeScript: `"strict": true` in `tsconfig.json`; no implicit any.
- Dependency pinning via `package-lock.json` / `pnpm-lock.yaml` / `yarn.lock`; commit the lockfile.
- Vulnerability scan via `npm audit` or `pnpm audit`; CI runs `npm audit --audit-level=high` and fails on high-severity findings.
- Secrets must not land in source; use `dotenv` for `.env` with `.env.example` checked in.
- ESM vs CommonJS: pick one at project bootstrap and be explicit in `package.json` `type` field.
- Publish packages with `.npmignore` or `files:` in `package.json` so internal tooling is not shipped.

## Universal ESE rules

The full set of ESE rules that apply to every project (artifact scaffolding, writing standards, commit discipline, release discipline, submodule upgrades) live in the canonical [AGENTS.md](.standards/starters/AGENTS.md) at `.standards/starters/AGENTS.md`. Read that file for cross-stack rules. This CLAUDE.md supplements it with TypeScript / Node-specific commands.
